         <abstract>
            <p>Let $f(x)$ be a monic irreducible polynomial in $\mathbf{Z}\lbrack x \rbrack$, and $\mathbf{r}$ a root of $f(x)$ in $\mathbf{C}$. Let $K$ be the field $\mathbf{Q}(\mathbf{r})$ and $\mathscr{R}$ the ring of integers in $K$. Then for some $k \in \mathbf{Z}, \operatorname{disc} \mathbf{r} = k^2 \operatorname{disc} \mathscr{R}$. In this paper we give constructive methods for (a) deciding if a prime $p$ divides $k$, and (b) if $p\mid k$, finding a polynomial $g(x) \in \mathbf{Z}\lbrack x \rbrack$ so that $g(x) \not\equiv 0 (\operatorname{mod} p)$ but $g(\mathbf{r})/p \in \mathscr{R}$.</p>
          </abstract>
